# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-3380
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food for occasions and celebrations"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-for-occasions-and-celebrations" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils taste a range of bread and explore different varieties from
  around the world. They examine how and why bread is eaten on special occasions, and plan
  and make a bread 'pocket' for a special occasion."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Bread is a staple food across the globe, available in a huge range of
  sizes, shapes, flavours and finishes. It also has deep cultural and religious significance.
  Through the context of bread, learning around the threads of Consumer awareness and Food
  culture are further developed from Year 1. Future units expand pupils' experience,
  introducing more unfamiliar foods, and global tastes and cuisines.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3380-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3380-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3380-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3380-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3380-5 ;
  curric:id "3380"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.220235Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3383
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food from plants and animals"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-from-plants-and-animals" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores food from plants and animals. Pupils sort food into plant and
  animal sources, and name a range of food from each source. This learning is extended
  through making a potato salad, highlighting the food source of each ingredient."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """All food is from plants or animals; learning about this ensures that
  pupils know where different food originates. Developing from Early Years Foundation Stage
  Early Learning Goals, The natural world and Creating with materials, this unit reinforces
  food origins and explores different types of food from each source. In Year 2 pupils examine
  how food is grown, reared and caught, as well as establish simple 'farm to fork' food chains.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3383-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3383-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3383-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3383-4 ;
  curric:id "3383"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.693792Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3378
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Cooking without heat"@en ;
  curric:slug "cooking-without-heat" ;
  rdfs:comment """During this unit, pupils continue to acquire and develop their food skills. Pupils
  learn about the structure of a recipe and how to use the 'bridge hold' and 'claw grip'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Developing food skills enables pupils to achieve greater accuracy and
  precision, helping their fine motor skills. Practical activity reinforces food safety and
  hygiene procedures and adherence. Food skills from Year 1, Let's start cooking, are
  revisited, and new skills and techniques are introduced. In Year 3, pupils prepare and cook
  more complex recipes and use the application of heat, as well as continue to improve their
  food skill repertoire.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3378-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3378-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3378-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3378-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3378-5 ;
  curric:id "3378"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.827829Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3381
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Let's start cooking"@en ;
  curric:slug "lets-start-cooking" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to food and gives them their first opportunity to
  prepare simple dishes. Pupils use different food skills and equipment, and learn about
  handling food safely and hygienically."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Knowing how to prepare and cook food equips us with the ability to create
  healthy dishes and meals, gaining food skills and knowledge which can be applied in the
  future. Learning is framed through familiar contexts and experiences from the Early Years
  Foundation Stage Early Learning Goals, such as managing self and language skills, are further
  developed. In future units, food skills are revisited to develop accuracy, and new skills
  introduced. A greater range of recipes from around the world are used to expand learning and
  provide different food experiences.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3381-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3381-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3381-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3381-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3381-5 ;
  curric:id "3381"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.045968Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3384
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food for me and you"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-for-me-and-you" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils taste a range of fruit and vegetables to develop their sensory
  skills. They explore why people eat different types of food, such as time of day or
  culture, and plan and make a salad for their family."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """What we eat and drink are influenced by many factors and understanding the
  context of these through tasting and family values enables us to make informed food
  decisions. These concepts are extended from the Early Years Foundation Stage Early Learning
  Goals, People, culture and communities, and Creating with materials, and introduce personal
  and family food preferences, culture and location. Factors affecting food choice are
  developed in Year 2, via the thread Consumer awareness, focusing on food occasions,
  celebrations and global cuisine.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3384-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3384-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3384-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3384-4 ;
  curric:id "3384"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.203701Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3382
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food and drink for life"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-and-drink-for-life" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on food and drink being essential for life. Pupils examine food
  preferences and the different factors of food choice, and make and evaluate a dish using
  their senses."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Having an appreciation of the importance of food and drink for our health
  is fundamental. It provides the sustenance for us to grow, be active and maintain health.
  Building on the Early Years Foundation Stage Early Learning Goals, Aspects of managing self,
  Personal, Social and Emotional Development, and Physical development, progress. In future
  units, the threads of Sensory evaluation and Healthy eating and nutrition are explored and
  enhanced, with the Eatwell Guide being introduced in Year 2.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3382-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3382-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3382-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3382-4 ;
  curric:id "3382"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.223726Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3379
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Where my food comes from"@en ;
  curric:slug "where-my-food-comes-from" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils explore the origins of foods, listing foods that are grown,
  reared and caught. They construct simple 'farm to fork' food chains showing how food
  changes from its origin to consumption."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Our food is grown, reared or caught. Knowing the origin of food, and how
  it is produced and changed from its origin to consumption, allows us to make informed
  choices. This builds on the Food origins and provenance thread in Year 1, that food is from
  plants and animals. This thread is further developed in Year 3, creating more complex 'farm
  to fork' food chains, and learning about different food origins and production around the
  world.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3379-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3379-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3379-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3379-4 ;
  curric:id "3379"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.236917Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-2607
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The Eatwell Guide: healthy eating"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-eatwell-guide-healthy-eating" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to The Eatwell Guide, exploring its key messages and
  food groups. The composition of healthy meals is examined, focusing on 5 A DAY and
  drinking plenty. Pupils use a range of food skills to make a healthy wrap based on the
  Eatwell Guide food groups."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The Eatwell Guide forms the basis of healthy eating advice to the UK
  population aged 5+ years; learning about this equips pupils with the ability to make healthy
  choices in life. Building on Year 1, food and drink being essential for life, the unit
  introduces the fundamental building blocks of healthy eating and drinking advice. In future,
  these principles will be revisited and explored further in Year 3, Food and drink choices,
  planning healthy meals for themselves and others, and food for special occasions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2607-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2607-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2607-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2607-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2607-5 ;
  curric:id "2607"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.260110Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

